8
00:00:37,699 --&gt; 00:00:42,350
So, Five Directions include all the directions in space.

9
00:00:42,726 --&gt; 00:00:46,731
After the theory of Five Directions, there was the theory of Five Materials.

10
00:00:47,058 --&gt; 00:00:49,453
Master Han in the Spring and Autumn period once said:

11
00:00:49,453 --&gt; 00:00:53,056
“There were five materials in the world. People should use all of them.”

12
00:00:53,838 --&gt; 00:00:55,957
So what are those Five Materials?

13
00:00:57,122 --&gt; 00:01:02,934
Five Materials refer to wood, fire, earth, gold and water. 

14
00:01:03,214 --&gt; 00:01:06,547
This is a kind of simple materialistic idea.

15
00:01:07,093 --&gt; 00:01:14,970
It tries to attribute all the tangible objects to five kinds and it confirms the materialism of the world.

16
00:01:15,611 --&gt; 00:01:28,282
In the Book of History, there is an item that reads “Water and Fire is what the people drink and eat; Metal and Wood is what the people used to make things; Earth, is where everything grows. “

17
00:01:29,026 --&gt; 00:01:37,488
It emphasizes that the Five Elements are closely related with our daily life.

18
00:01:38,138 --&gt; 00:01:39,419
How can we understand that?

19
00:01:39,419 --&gt; 00:01:43,211
As it is known to all, Water is the source of life.

20
00:01:43,494 --&gt; 00:01:46,676
70% of the body is made of water.

21
00:01:46,854 --&gt; 00:01:51,310
