22
00:01:51,630 --&gt; 00:01:55,378
As well as the carrier of releasing waste in the body.

23
00:01:55,378 --&gt; 00:02:00,365
So, water is vital for life.

24
00:02:00,735 --&gt; 00:02:05,676
&quot;Ancestor Sui drilled wood for fire&quot;, which has totally changed our way of drinking and eating.

25
00:02:05,905 --&gt; 00:02:10,161
Since then, people have lived life totally different with the wild animals. 

26
00:02:11,512 --&gt; 00:02:17,716
We can take the nutrition from food more efficient. The better way of eating helps us to be healthier and to breed more children.

27
00:02:17,938 --&gt; 00:02:25,231
Our ancestor You Chao used metal and wood to build houses, which totally changed our way of living in the cave.

28
00:02:25,558 --&gt; 00:02:27,627
He improved our housing conditions.

29
00:02:27,847 --&gt; 00:02:35,224
So Five Materials are important for our body as well as our life.

30
00:02:35,827 --&gt; 00:02:39,950
They reduces the harm caused by the harsh conditions.

31
00:02:40,366 --&gt; 00:02:44,333
With the development of productivity, people enter the stage of agrarian society.

32
00:02:44,597 --&gt; 00:02:49,865
People cultivated crops on the arable land to guarantee the source of food.

33
00:02:50,091 --&gt; 00:02:53,661
In the last thousands of years, earth is the root of life.

34
00:02:53,986 --&gt; 00:02:59,004
Reasons above can easily explain why our ancestors paid great attention to the Five Materials.

35
00:02:59,324 --&gt; 00:03:06,804
However, ancient Chinese furthered the nature of the Five Materials by distilling the theory.

36
00:03:07,134 --&gt; 00:03:13,728
They tried to explain other phenomena by categorizing them into the five elements.

37
00:03:14,194 --&gt; 00:03:16,725
The Book of History has mentioned the Five Elements in one Chapter:

38
00:03:16,725 --&gt; 00:03:24,121
There are Five Elements: Water, Fire, Wood, Metal and Earth.

39
00:03:24,631 --&gt; 00:03:35,322
Water flows down and wet things, fire heats things above it, wood can be straight or bended, metal can be made into different shapes and crops can grow on earth.

40
00:03:36,297 --&gt; 00:03:44,035
Water becomes salty when it flows down, bitter smell emits when something is in fire, sour taste is created by the flexible wood, spicy taste is produced by the metal and sweet taste is made from crops.

41
00:03:44,825 --&gt; 00:03:53,806
This explanation further explains the features of the Five Elements.

42
00:03:54,452 --&gt; 00:04:00,389
It tries to relate the Five Elements with the Five tastes.

43
00:04:00,566 --&gt; 00:04:02,817
How to understand the connection?

44
00:04:03,612 --&gt; 00:04:05,235
Let us start with the Wood.

45
00:04:05,610 --&gt; 00:04:10,854
“Wood can be straight or bended” means that trees grow straight or bended.

46
00:04:11,265 --&gt; 00:04:18,826
Other features like being flexible can be attributed to the features of wood.

47
00:04:18,998 --&gt; 00:04:26,902
The idea of &quot;straight or winding&quot; is the posture of the trunks that grow upward and the branches that stretch outside.

48
00:04:27,142 --&gt; 00:04:34,915
This can be used to described the objects and phenomena which were growing, developing or stretching.

49
00:04:34,915 --&gt; 00:04:39,885
All those features can be attributed to wood.

50
00:04:40,906 --&gt; 00:04:43,029
“Heating things above” is the feature of fire.

51
00:04:43,201 --&gt; 00:04:50,258
&quot;Fire heats things above it&quot; means that warmth, ascension and brightness are the features of fire.

52
00:04:50,389 --&gt; 00:04:55,740
“Heating things above” refers to the feature of fire that its heat pass upward.

53
00:04:55,967 --&gt; 00:05:06,862
So, the elements of fire can be extended to all the features of warmth, ascension, brightness and fertilization.

54
00:05:07,040 --&gt; 00:05:12,127
“Crops can grow” refers to cultivating on the arable land.

55
00:05:12,300 --&gt; 00:05:18,195
Receiving, bearing and growing are the features of Earth.

56
00:05:18,320 --&gt; 00:05:22,761
“Jia” here means land and “Qiang” means harvest.

57
00:05:22,942 --&gt; 00:05:29,565
“Jia Qiang” means that people can cultivate and harvest on the land.
58
00:05:30,350 --&gt; 00:05:40,480
All the ability or phenomena of receiving, bearing and growing can be categorized into the features of Earth.

59
00:05:40,792 --&gt; 00:05:43,261
So, people value the Earth a lot.

60
00:05:43,445 --&gt; 00:05:52,359
We have the proverb like “Earth bears the other four Elements”, “All the things are born and dead in the earth” and “Earth is the mother of everything.

61
00:05:53,096 --&gt; 00:05:55,614
Then let us analyse the features of Metal

62
00:05:56,355 --&gt; 00:05:59,778
“Cong Ge” has the meaning of change and killing.

63
00:05:59,869 --&gt; 00:06:11,392
The features of Metal can be extended to explain all the objects or phenomena that contain the meaning of killing, degrading, constraint or cleaning.” 

64
00:06:12,336 --&gt; 00:06:23,626
“Run Xia” means that water owns the features of moisture,  going downward, coldness and hiding

65
00:06:23,848 --&gt; 00:06:27,837
“Run Xia” means that water owns the features of going own and moistening things.

66
00:06:27,837 --&gt; 00:06:39,452
The features of water are extended to all the objects or phenomena that implies coldness, moisture, going down and hiding. 

67
00:06:40,293 --&gt; 00:06:47,760
Through simple materialistic analysis, the ancient Chinese generalized the features of the Five Materials in the philosophic way.

68
00:06:47,760 --&gt; 00:06:56,264
Deducing in this way, ancient Chinese also analyze the nature of something more complicated inn the five aspects.

69
00:06:56,645 --&gt; 00:06:58,541
In the book of National History- Zheng, 

70
00:06:58,541 --&gt; 00:07:05,550
“ The ancient king mixed earth with metal, wood, water and fire to form everything.”

71
00:07:06,240 --&gt; 00:07:12,940
All the things in the world is created by the reaction among the Five Elemtns.

72
00:07:14,014 --&gt; 00:07:22,856
